✨progress not perfection✨

 As a gymnast, you get your power from running/hurdling into your tumbling pass. 

In cheer, learning to tumble from a few steps into a tumbling pass has been quit the challenge for me… as you can see a little leg separation in my tumbling😭

In gymnastics, your goal is to get your numbers in.. to perfect your tumbling, which is why gymnasts train so many hours. 

I’m slowly learning to change my mindset, to let go of perfectionism, and to be proud of my progress today as a cheerleader:)

How do cheerleaders not run into each other tumbling?🫣 

Counting and staying on count is super important in competitive cheer. It syncs choreography and tumbling when so much is happening in a routine. This was quite the challenge switching from gymnastics. 

I love it when the crowd counts along with us. We feed off of the energy and excitement in the room.
